Package hu.bme.mit.theta.core.type.inttype

Integer type and its expressions. Use IntExprs to create them. Note that this is a (mathematical) SMT integer, with an unbounded range (long in the implementation) and no overflows. - IntType: the actual integer type. - IntLitExpr: integer literal - IntNegExpr: unary minus - IntPosExpr: unary plus - IntAddExpr: addition - IntSubExpr: subtraction - IntMulExpr: multiplication - IntDivExpr: integer division - IntModExpr: modulus - IntRemExpr: remainder - IntEqExpr: equal - IntNegExpr: not equal - IntGtExpr: greater - IntLtExpr: less - IntGeqExpr: greater or equal - IntLeqExpr: less or equal - IntToRatExpr: cast to rational
